he refills his can then waters it.\nSo, the total number of times they have to refill to water all the plants is 0 + 0 + 1 + 0 = 1.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\nInput: plants = [2,2,3,3], capacityA = 3, capacityB = 4\nOutput: 2\nExplanation:\n- Initially, Alice and Bob have 3 units and 4 units of water in their watering cans respectively.\n- Alice waters plant 0, Bob waters plant 3.\n- Alice and Bob now have 1 unit of water each, and need to water plants 1 and 2 respectively.\n- Since neither of them have enough water for their current plants, they refill their cans and then water the plants.\nSo, the total number of times they have to refill to water all the plants is 0 + 1 + 1 + 0 = 2.\n\n**Example 3:**\n\nInput: plants = [5], capacityA = 10, capacityB = 8\nOutput: 0\nExplanation:\n- There is only one plant.\n- Alice's watering can has 10 units of water, whereas Bob's can has 8 units. Since Alice has more water in her can, she waters this plant.\nSo, the total number of times they have to refill is 0.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `n == plants.length`\n\n- `1 <= n <= 10⁵`\n\n- `1 <= plants[i] <= 10⁶`\n\n- `max(plants[i]) <= capacityA, capacityB <= 10⁹`","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/watering-plants-ii/","problemName":"Watering Plants II","problemNumber":2105,"problemSlug":"watering-plants-ii","schemaVersion":2,"sequenceIndex":2105,"solutionApproaches":[]},{"assets":[{"assetIndex":0,"bytes":10603,"contentType":"image/png","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/2106-maximum-fruits-harvested-after-at-most-k-steps/2106-1.png","originalUrl":"../../../images/2106-1.png","sha256":"fa8cbd084be8f635a8f5f6e1115be69c152693f3aae5746348fe4db3fa4ce99d"},{"assetIndex":1,"bytes":11738,"contentType":"image/png","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/2106-maximum-fruits-harvested-after-at-most-k-steps/2106-2.png","originalUrl":"../../../images/2106-2.png","sha256":"392bfd5babbc53f1eb08f8314ec84aaaee9867576b936d1793e395b9cba2c450"},{"assetIndex":2,"bytes":9545,"contentType":"image/png","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/2106-maximum-fruits-harvested-after-at-most-k-steps/2106-3.png","originalUrl":"../../../images/2106-3.png","sha256":"e86045818e29f5aa4821439963d8c85c1cf4b5ed3fe8d6bc5416c6354bf4493b"}],"categories":["Array","Binary Search","Sliding Window","Prefix Sum"],"constraintBlocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"Fruits are available at some positions on an infinite x-axis. You are given a 2D integer array `fruits` where `fruits[i] = [positioni, amounti]` depicts `amounti` fruits at the position `positioni`. `fruits` is already **sorted** by `positioni` in **ascending order**, and each `positioni` is **unique**.\n\nYou are also given an integer `startPos` and an integer `k`. Initially, you are at the position `startPos`. From any position, you can either walk to the **left or right**. It takes **one step** to move **one unit** on the x-axis, and you can walk **at most** `k` steps in total. For every position you reach, you harvest all the fruits at that position, and the fruits will disappear from that position.\n\nReturn *the **maximum total number** of fruits you can harvest*.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"alt":"Problem image","contentType":"image/png","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/2106-maximum-fruits-harvested-after-at-most-k-steps/2106-1.png","sequence":1,"sha256":"fa8cbd084be8f635a8f5f6e1115be69c152693f3aae5746348fe4db3fa4ce99d","type":"image"},{"sequence":2,"text":"Input: fruits = [[2,8],[6,3],[8,6]], startPos = 5, k = 4\nOutput: 9\nExplanation: \nThe optimal way is to:\n- Move right to position 6 and harvest 3 fruits\n- Move right to position 8 and harvest 6 fruits\nYou moved 3 steps and harvested 3 + 6 = 9 fruits in total.","type":"code"},{"sequence":3,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"alt":"Problem image","contentType":"image/png","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/2106-maximum-fruits-harvested-after-at-most-k-steps/2106-2.png","sequence":4,"sha256":"392bfd5babbc53f1e