er walk to the **left or right**. It takes **one step** to move **one unit** on the x-axis, and you can walk **at most** `k` steps in total. For every position you reach, you harvest all the fruits at that position, and the fruits will disappear from that position.\n\nReturn *the **maximum total number** of fruits you can harvest*.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\n[[img:leetcode_seed/assets/problems/2106-maximum-fruits-harvested-after-at-most-k-steps/2106-1.png]]\n\nInput: fruits = [[2,8],[6,3],[8,6]], startPos = 5, k = 4\nOutput: 9\nExplanation: \nThe optimal way is to:\n- Move right to position 6 and harvest 3 fruits\n- Move right to position 8 and harvest 6 fruits\nYou moved 3 steps and harvested 3 + 6 = 9 fruits in total.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\n[[img:leetcode_seed/assets/problems/2106-maximum-fruits-harvested-after-at-most-k-steps/2106-2.png]]\n\nInput: fruits = [[0,9],[4,1],[5,7],[6,2],[7,4],[10,9]], startPos = 5, k = 4\nOutput: 14\nExplanation: \nYou can move at most k = 4 steps, so you cannot reach position 0 nor 10.\nThe optimal way is to:\n- Harvest the 7 fruits at the starting position 5\n- Move left to position 4 and harvest 1 fruit\n- Move right to position 6 and harvest 2 fruits\n- Move right to position 7 and harvest 4 fruits\nYou moved 1 + 3 = 4 steps and harvested 7 + 1 + 2 + 4 = 14 fruits in total.\n\n**Example 3:**\n\n[[img:leetcode_seed/assets/problems/2106-maximum-fruits-harvested-after-at-most-k-steps/2106-3.png]]\n\nInput: fruits = [[0,3],[6,4],[8,5]], startPos = 3, k = 2\nOutput: 0\nExplanation:\nYou can move at most k = 2 steps and cannot reach any position with fruits.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= fruits.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `fruits[i].length == 2`\n\n- `0 <= startPos, positioni <= 2 * 10⁵`\n\n- `positioni-1 < positioni` for any `i > 0` (**0-indexed**)\n\n- `1 <= amounti <= 10⁴`\n\n- `0 <= k <= 2 * 10⁵`","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/maximum-fruits-harvested-after-at-most-k-steps/","problemName":"Maximum Fruits Harvested After at Most K St