`'1'`.","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/minimum-time-to-remove-all-cars-containing-illegal-goods/","problemName":"Minimum Time to Remove All Cars Containing Illegal Goods","problemNumber":2167,"problemSlug":"minimum-time-to-remove-all-cars-containing-illegal-goods","schemaVersion":2,"sequenceIndex":2167,"solutionApproaches":[]},{"assets":[],"categories":["Hash Table","String","Counting","Hash Function","Rolling Hash"],"constraintBlocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"Given a digit string `s`, return *the number of **unique substrings **of *`s`* where every digit appears the same number of times.*\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: s = \"1212\"\nOutput: 5\nExplanation: The substrings that meet the requirements are \"1\", \"2\", \"12\", \"21\", \"1212\".\nNote that although the substring \"12\" appears twice, it is only counted once.","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: s = \"12321\"\nOutput: 9\nExplanation: The substrings that meet the requirements are \"1\", \"2\", \"3\", \"12\", \"23\", \"32\", \"21\", \"123\", \"321\".","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= s.length <= 1000`\n\n- `s` consists of digits.","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["Hash Table","String","Counting","Hash Function","Rolling Hash"],"createdAt":0,"difficulty":"Medium","lastRevisionAt":0,"problem":"Given a digit string `s`, return *the number of **unique substrings **of *`s`* where every digit appears the same number of times.*\n\n**Example 1:**\n\nInput: s = \"1212\"\nOutput: 5\nExplanation: The substrings that meet the requirements are \"1\", \"2\", \"12\", \"21\", \"1212\".\nNote that although the substring \"12\" appears twice, it is only counted once.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\nInput: s = \"12321\"\nOutput: 9\nExplanation: The substrings that meet the requirements are \"1\", \"2\", \"3\", \"12\", \"23\", \"32